&lt;/h1>
&lt;p>Paatra in Sanskrit means pot, &lt;br>
but it also means an eligible person. &lt;br>
Paatrata means eligibility, capacity, &lt;br>
capability to hold what is given to you.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>You can ask for anything, knowledge, money power. &lt;br>
This is part of your imagination. &lt;br>
But fortunately if your wish is fulfilled &lt;br>
and that knowledge, money or power &lt;br>
is given to you then can you hold it &lt;br>
gracefully, happily and for the benefits of all around?&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>